1) There are 2 types in pipes in angualar

a) built-in pipes
b) custom pipes

Examples of some of the built ib pipes:

1) datepipe - {{ today | date:'short' }}
2) UpperCasePipe / LowerCasePipe → text casing - {{ 'angular' | uppercase }} <!-- Output: ANGULAR -->
3) CurrencyPipe → formats currency values. - {{ 1500 | currency:'USD' }}
4) DecimalPipe → formats numbers. - {{ 3.14159 | number:'1.2-2' }} <!-- Output: 3.14 -->
5) PercentPipe → formats numbers as percentages. -> {{ 0.25 | percent }} <!-- Output: 25% -->
7) JsonPipe → converts an object to JSON. = {{ obj | json }}
8) SlicePipe → slices arrays or strings. - {{ [1,2,3,4,5] | slice:1:3 }} <!-- Output: [2,3] -->

These topics covered on Pipes

So in short:

Built-in Pipes

Custom Pipes

Pure vs Impure

Pipe Chaining

Parameters in Pipes

Async Pipe

Performance & Best Practices


